glossaryTerms.definition: In computer programming, an application programming interface (API) is a set of subroutine definitions, communication protocols, and tools for building software.

VirusTotal is a website created by the Spanish security company Hispasec Sistemas. Launched in June 2004, it was acquired by Google Inc. in September 2012.The company's ownership switched in January 2018 to Chronicle, a subsidiary of Alphabet Inc..

meta.title: Errors

doc.title: Errors
doc.body:
The VirusTotal API follows the conventional HTTP response codes to indicate success or failure. Codes in the `2xx` range indicate success. Codes in the `4xx` range indicate an error in the request (e.g. a missing parameter, a resource was not found). Codes in the `5xx` range indicate an error in VirusTotal's servers and should be rare.

Unsuccessful requests return additional information about the error in JSON format.
[block:code]
{
  "codes": [
    {
      "code": "{\n  \"error\": {\n    \"code\": \"<error code>\",\n    \"message\": \"<a message describing the error>\"\n  }\n}",
      "language": "json",
      "name": "An error response"
    },
    {
      "code": "{\n  \"error\": {\n    \"code\": \"NotFoundError\",\n    \"message\": \"URL \\\"thisurlidmakesnosenseatall\\\" not found\"\n  }\n}",
      "language": "json",
      "name": "Example (404)"
    },
    {
      "code": "{\n  \"error\": {\n    \"code\": \"AuthenticationRequiredError\",\n    \"message\": \"X-Apikey header is missing\"\n  }\n}",
      "language": "json",
      "name": "Example (401)"
    }
  ]
}
[/block]

[block:textarea]
{
  "text": "The error `code` is a string with one of the values provided in the table below. The `message` usually provides a little more information about the error.",

}
[/block]

codes.code:
import requests
import io
import bz2
import json

url = "https://www.virustotal.com/api/v3/feeds/files/{time}"


response = requests.get(
    url.format(time="202002070300"),
    headers={'x-apikey': '<your VT API key>'})

if response.status_code != 200:
  raise Exception(response.content)
else:
  with io.BytesIO(response.content) as f:
    file_feed = [json.loads(line) for line in bz2.decompress(f.read()).splitlines()]
# further processing

children.title: Get a per-minute file feed batch

codes.code:
import requests
import io
import tarfile
import json

url = "https://www.virustotal.com/api/v3/feeds/files/hourly/{time}"

response = requests.get(
    url.format(time="2021012211"),
    headers={'x-apikey': '<your VT API key>'})

if response.status_code != 200:
  raise Exception(response.content)
else:
  file_feed = []
  with io.BytesIO(response.content) as f:
    with tarfile.open(fileobj=f, mode='r:bz2')as t:
      # process minutely batches
      for batch in t.getmembers():
        file_feed.extend([json.loads(line) for line in t.extractfile(batch)])
  # further processing
codes.name: Python
